title: Four die in Subang Jaya fire
text:
More 
Four people were found dead in a house in USJ 2, Subang Jaya, which was almost completely destroyed by a fire early today. 
Bernama quoted Selangor Fire and Rescue Department assistant director of operations Mohd Sani Harul saying three bodies were found in a bedroom of the double-storey house at Jalan USJ 2/5A while the fourth was in a bathroom. 
The identities of the dead have yet to be established. 
Mohd Sani said the house was 80 percent destroyed in the fire that started about 5.30am. 
"The fire was brought under control at about 6am. Sixteen officers and personnel from the Subang Jaya and Section 7 fire and rescue stations put out the blaze," he said. 
- Bernama
